Unable to Access Internal HR Portal While Working Remotely
Issue

A remote employee was unable to access the company's internal HR portal (hr.corp.local) to approve leave requests. The browser displayed "This site can't be reached", while all public websites loaded successfully.

Business Impact

The employee could not access internal HR systems, preventing them from approving employee PTO requests.

Troubleshooting Performed
Confirmed the user was working remotely.
Verified the URL was hr.corp.local.
Confirmed internet connectivity by browsing public websites.
Tested using another web browser.
Reproduced the issue.
Resolution
Connected to the user's computer using Remote Support.
Verified that the HR portal could not be reached.
Opened the VPN client.
Found the VPN was disconnected.
Connected to the corporate VPN.
Refreshed the HR portal.
Confirmed the portal loaded successfully and the user regained access.
Root Cause

The HR portal is hosted on the organization's internal network and is only accessible while connected to the corporate VPN. The user attempted to access it while disconnected.

Prevention
Remind remote users to connect to the VPN before accessing internal resources.
Consider configuring the VPN to connect automatically when users sign in remotely.
Skills Demonstrated
VPN troubleshooting
Internal DNS resolution
Remote support
Network connectivity troubleshooting
User verification and issue validation
Lessons Learned

A .corp.local address is an internal domain. If a remote user cannot reach a *.corp.local website but public websites work normally, the VPN connection should be one of the first things checked.
